    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nEver since i upgraded to neovim v0.12 this option in vimrc, to force vim not to change the terminal cursor does not work anymore. it worked perfectly in neovim v0.11:\n\nvim.opt.guicursor = ''\n\nthe result is when i exit the terminal the cursor is also a block pointer which is very disturbing. Why do the defaults even change the pointer at all? If we just keep the original terminal cursor as default i bet the chances of getting it right in neovim too improves.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\ncat .config/nvim/init.vim\nvim.opt.guicursor = ''\n\nnvim\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nthis option should work as it did before\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOs / Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niterm2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbrew or nixpkgs",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "\n\nI can reproduce this issue by \n\n1. changing my terminal's cursor to \"vertical\"\n2. `nvim --clean --cmd 'set guicursor='`\n3. the cursor is changed to \"block\" but should be \"vertical\". \n\n`:help 'guicursor'` documents:\n\n\tTo disable cursor-styling, reset the option: >vim\n\t\tset guicursor=\n\n\nrelated?:\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36261\n\n> Why do the defaults even change the pointer at all?\n\nbecause 95% of users like the 'guicursor' default, and it's obviously better, despite your personal tastes?\n\n>  If we just keep the original terminal cursor as default i bet the chances of getting it right in neovim too improves.\n\nHow would that work while also having different cursor shapes for e.g. insert-mode?",
