            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> I can reproduce this issue by\n>       1. changing my terminal's cursor to \"vertical\"\n>       2. `nvim --clean --cmd 'set guicursor='`\n>       3. the cursor is changed to \"block\" but should be \"vertical\".\n\nI believe this behavior is because of Unibilium and/or terminfo defs. See the description on #38219. If we sent out a `\\x1b[0 q`, that's technically the command to reset to default, but is inconsistent across terminal implementations. Unibilium has `\\x1b[2 q` for Ghostty's reset cursor style command, which actually sets steady block, not necessarily what the user has set.",
            "created_at": "2026-04-15T23:37:04Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38987#issuecomment-4256399195",
